# Never Crop Vector Text

Vector text in `web-main/` and `app/` navs, headers, and composite SVG crops must never be clipped at the top or bottom.

## Rule

- Do not ship a crop, mask, `overflow: hidden`, `translateY`, or aspect-ratio window that trims any part of a vector word.
- Match mobile header spacing to the approved reference first, then widen/tall the crop window until all vector rows are fully visible.
- If removing upper rows from a composite SVG, crop between rows, not through glyphs.

## Required check

Before finishing a crop/case-header/mobile-nav change:

- Verify the first visible row is fully intact at the top edge
- Verify the last visible row is fully intact at the bottom edge
- If either edge clips text, increase the visible window or adjust the crop until no letters are cut off

## For this portfolio

- Home-page mobile header spacing is the reference for case-page mobile headers unless Sam explicitly asks otherwise.
- "Close enough" is not acceptable for vector text crops; all glyphs must clear the crop boundary.
